{
  "stem": "19218.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 249.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean, we could not do the work outside and do the painting.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So we were always taken inside.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They always had enough pipes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I don't know what in the hell they-- they had going through the pipes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It must have been some gas or so.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I know that the pipes were also refrigerated, which means they were always cold and you could see ice forming on them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So I had no idea what they were in there-- doing there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I went to my kapo.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His name was Kapo Louis, I don't remember his last name-- although I looked for him after the war because he was-- he was really-- although he was German and he was a prisoner, but he was a political prisoner.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the political prisoners are like-- I believe he must have been a Communist or so, that's why he was in concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he was a very fair man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I-- knowing that my brother will-- eventually he'll-- he'll just give up, I went to the kapo and I told him this is the only relative I have in my life.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were-- we were three young boys, the youngest one of the group in there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One is still in Chicago today, Morris, he's around here, and the other one is in Israel.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "His name is Joshua.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were working together and we were always getting the easiest jobs because he would assign the jobs what to do.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they would always give us an extra quart of water or an extra quart of soup because we were the youngest ones.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
